The paper deals with data structures for approximate similarity search, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The use of locality sensitive hashing (LSH) is a common technique for solving this problem, and the paper proposes a new LSH-based data structure that guarantees no false negatives. This makes it relevant to the data structures (cs.DS), information theory (cs.IT), computational geometry (cs.CG), databases (cs.DB), and data mining (cs.DM) sub-categories.
